Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.00,0:00:00.00,DCMain,,0000,0000,0000,,Detective Conan Episode 781 \N"The Scarlet Intersection"
Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.00,0:00:05.00,DCMain,,0000,0000,0000,,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:01.40,0:00:08.48,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Investigator Jodie's friend Shibuya Natsuko-san\Nwas attacked and rendered unconscious.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:09.76,0:00:15.82,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,When we rushed to help, three \Nsuspects were called in, and...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:16.61,0:00:17.99,DCMain,AMURO,0000,0000,0000,,I didn't have a choice.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:19.54,0:00:23.62,DCMain,AMURO,0000,0000,0000,,She asked me to investigate her stalker.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:23.89,0:00:26.04,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Bourbon?!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:26.67,0:00:32.12,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Later, Bourbon and I determined \Nthe identity of the culprit.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:32.97,0:00:34.68,DCMain,TEACHER B,0000,0000,0000,,E-Excuse me!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:34.90,0:00:36.93,DCMain,TEACHER B,0000,0000,0000,,The hospital just called!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:36.93,0:00:41.00,DCMain,TEACHER B,0000,0000,0000,,Shibuya-sensei's condition has \Nworsened, and her life is in danger!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:42.08,0:00:44.14,DCItalic,JODIE,0000,0000,0000,,N-Natsuko!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:49.70,0:00:50.52,DCMain,JODIE,0000,0000,0000,,Natsuko!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:52.88,0:00:55.84,DCMain,NATSUKO,0000,0000,0000,,Jodie, you came.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:55.84,0:00:56.78,DCMain,JODIE,0000,0000,0000,,Y-Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:57.09,0:01:00.47,DCMain,NATSUKO,0000,0000,0000,,I'm surprised you knew I \Nregained consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:00.47,0:01:01.41,DCMain,JODIE,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:01.64,0:01:09.34,DCMain,NATSUKO,0000,0000,0000,,It's partially my fault this happened, \Nso I asked them not to tell the school.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:09.34,0:01:10.95,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,This is bad!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:10.95,0:01:12.30,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Jodie-sensei!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:12.30,0:01:13.63,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Where's Investigator Camel?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:13.80,0:01:16.13,DCMain,JODIE,0000,0000,0000,,What? Probably with the car.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:18.79,0:01:20.43,DCMain,CAMEL,0000,0000,0000,,Kusuda Rikumichi?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:20.81,0:01:23.12,DCMain,CAMEL,0000,0000,0000,,Don't know him.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:23.12,0:01:25.45,DCMain,AMURO,0000,0000,0000,,He was a patient at this hospital.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:25.45,0:01:29.13,DCMain,AMURO,0000,0000,0000,,He abandoned his car nearby and disappeared.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:29.95,0:01:32.51,DCMain,AMURO,0000,0000,0000,,I think there's a gun involved.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:32.51,0:01:35.14,DCMain,AMURO,0000,0000,0000,,Have you heard anything?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:35.14,0:01:36.36,DCMain,CAMEL,0000,0000,0000,,Who knows?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:36.36,0:01:37.45,DCMain,AMURO,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, right.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:38.02,0:01:42.95,DCMain,AMURO,0000,0000,0000,,The information didn't make it down \Nto a lowly investigator like yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:43.47,0:01:45.05,DCMain,CAMEL,0000,0000,0000,,What are you talking about?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:45.05,0:01:47.37,DCMain,CAMEL,0000,0000,0000,,We always share our—
Dialogue: 0,0:01:47.37,0:01:48.76,DCMain,JODIE,0000,0000,0000,,Camel!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:48.76,0:01:50.38,DCMain,JODIE,0000,0000,0000,,What are you doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:50.59,0:01:52.56,DCMain,JODIE,0000,0000,0000,,Don't wander off by yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:54.73,0:01:55.59,DCMain,AMURO,0000,0000,0000,,Tsk.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:58.48,0:02:01.44,DCMain,JODIE,0000,0000,0000,,I hope you didn't tell him about Kusuda.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:01.44,0:02:02.89,DCMain,CAMEL,0000,0000,0000,,Of course not.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:03.19,0:02:06.69,DCMain,CAMEL,0000,0000,0000,,I'd never tell him he \Nshot himself in the car.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:06.69,0:02:09.48,DCMain,CAMEL,0000,0000,0000,,My lips are sealed.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:10.20,0:02:12.73,DCMain,JODIE,0000,0000,0000,,I see. Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:12.89,0:02:19.99,DCMain,CAMEL,0000,0000,0000,,It happened before I was assigned to \NJapan, so I heard about it from Akai-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.92,0:02:21.99,DCMain,CAMEL,0000,0000,0000,,Jodie-san?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:23.33,0:02:24.55,DCMain,CAMEL,0000,0000,0000,,Where are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:25.78,0:02:27.02,DCMain,CAMEL,0000,0000,0000,,Jodie-san?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.63,0:02:33.21,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Propelled forward by the \Nyears spent together.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.63,0:02:35.46,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Charging full speed ahead \Nwithout slowing the pace.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.46,0:02:37.17,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,What happened then?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.17,0:02:38.84,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,A suspicious pair have a \Ndangerous conversation!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:39.11,0:02:42.55,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Always determining the one truth with the \Nbody of a child and the mind of an adult,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.55,0:02:44.89,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,his name is Detective Conan!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.50,0:04:40.88,DCNote,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,Raiha Pass
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.15,0:05:06.15,DCEpTitle,EPTITLE,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(400,1)}The Scarlet Intersection
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.98,0:05:03.06,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,The Scarlet Intersection!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.15,0:05:08.66,DCNote,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,Haido Central Hospital
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.24,0:05:08.66,Previous,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(700,1)}The Previous Day
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.42,0:05:11.20,DCItalic,CAMEL,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.74,0:05:15.87,DCMain,CAMEL,0000,0000,0000,,Jodie-san?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.12,0:05:25.11,DCMain,JODIE,0000,0000,0000,,Camel!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.98,0:05:27.36,DCMain,CAMEL,0000,0000,0000,,Jodie-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.18,0:05:29.53,DCMain,JODIE,0000,0000,0000,,Is everything okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.99,0:05:32.39,DCMain,CAMEL,0000,0000,0000,,What do you mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.84,0:05:35.10,DCMain,JODIE,0000,0000,0000,,Amuro's a member of the Organization.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.57,0:05:38.98,DCMain,JODIE,0000,0000,0000,,We saw his car leaving the hospital.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.37,0:05:43.36,DCMain,JODIE,0000,0000,0000,,He didn't sweet talk any \Nsecrets out of you, did he?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.72,0:05:45.68,DCMain,CAMEL,0000,0000,0000,,N-No.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.68,0:05:48.45,DCMain,CAMEL,0000,0000,0000,,Didn't you just say that?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.80,0:05:50.68,DCMain,JODIE,0000,0000,0000,,What do you mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.27,0:05:54.12,DCMain,CAMEL,0000,0000,0000,,You said the exact same thing a moment ago...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.35,0:05:56.04,DCMain,JODIE,0000,0000,0000,,What are you talking about?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.04,0:06:00.53,DCMain,JODIE,0000,0000,0000,,I just got here from Natsuko's room!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.53,0:06:01.34,DCMain,CAMEL,0000,0000,0000,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.83,0:06:05.14,DCMain,CAMEL,0000,0000,0000,,Then, when I saw you earlier...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.74,0:06:09.97,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,A voice and disguise that \Ncould fool an acquaintance.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.15,0:06:14.60,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,There's only one woman...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.37,0:06:19.73,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,...with both.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.93,0:06:35.04,DCMain,AMURO,0000,0000,0000,,You're late.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.28,0:06:37.66,DCMain,AMURO,0000,0000,0000,,I thought you weren't coming.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.00,0:06:44.63,DCMain,VERMOUTH,0000,0000,0000,,I had trouble finding a scarf like hers.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.04,0:06:46.25,DCMain,AMURO,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.90,0:06:55.01,DCMain,AMURO,0000,0000,0000,,So, how'd it go?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.17,0:06:57.77,DCMain,VERMOUTH,0000,0000,0000,,Your man Kusuda...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.05,0:07:00.35,DCMain,VERMOUTH,0000,0000,0000,,You were right.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.45,0:07:09.88,DCMain,VERMOUTH,0000,0000,0000,,He shot himself.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.10,0:07:15.40,DCMain,VERMOUTH,0000,0000,0000,,Inside his own car.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.25,0:07:20.93,DCMain,AMURO,0000,0000,0000,,So... That is what happened after all...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.42,0:07:24.13,DCMain,CAMEL,0000,0000,0000,,What? Vermouth?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.39,0:07:34.68,DCMain,CAMEL,0000,0000,0000,,The Jodie-san I saw earlier \Nwas her disguised as you?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.55,0:07:38.86,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Bourbon must have asked you something.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.86,0:07:42.69,DCMain,CAMEL,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, but I didn't tell him anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.09,0:07:49.44,DCMain,CAMEL,0000,0000,0000,,He tried to shake me by saying the info\Nhadn't reached a lowly investigator like me.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.73,0:07:53.03,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,He provoked you so you'd relax your guard
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.03,0:07:57.65,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,and let something slip\Nwhen Jodie-sensei showed up.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.05,0:08:00.59,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,He manipulated you.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.43,0:08:03.38,DCMain,JODIE,0000,0000,0000,,H-Hold on.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.38,0:08:08.59,DCMain,JODIE,0000,0000,0000,,Does that mean Vermouth knew we'd \Ncome here and was waiting for us?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.78,0:08:09.65,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.06,0:08:14.22,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Everything's gone according to \NBourbon and Vermouth's plan.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.79,0:08:16.97,DCMain,JODIE,0000,0000,0000,,What do you mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.29,0:08:22.77,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,It started with the e-mail you \Nreceived from Shibuya-sensei.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.97,0:08:27.52,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Their scheme started there.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.52,0:08:31.28,DCMain,JODIE,0000,0000,0000,,Her invitation to go drinking?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.23,0:08:31.28,Invite,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,Subject: Invitation\NLet's go drinking!\NNatsuko
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.85,0:08:36.98,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,You said Shibuya-sensei didn't \Nremember sending that e-mail, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.98,0:08:38.66,DCMain,JODIE,0000,0000,0000,,Y-Yes...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.10,0:08:45.85,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Then Bourbon probably sent it \Nfrom Shibuya-sensei's phone.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.85,0:08:46.42,DCMain,JODIE,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.77,0:08:52.17,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Stealing a phone from an FBI \Ninvestigator sounds difficult.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.42,0:08:58.18,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,But taking a grade school teacher's \Nphone unnoticed was probably easy.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.39,0:09:02.64,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,If he'd met with Shibuya-sensei \Nseveral times as a detective,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.65,0:09:05.26,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,he would've had plenty of chances.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.26,0:09:08.19,DCMain,JODIE,0000,0000,0000,,But why would he send that message?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.58,0:09:17.07,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,So you'd call Shibuya-sensei \Nusing Investigator Camel's phone.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.59,0:09:19.32,DCMain,CAMEL,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.68,0:09:22.33,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,If you're going drinking, you'll meet at night.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.83,0:09:27.83,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,He knew your phone would be dead by then.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.43,0:09:30.16,DCMain,JOODIE,0000,0000,0000,,They were watching us.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.16,0:09:32.71,DCMain,CAMEL,0000,0000,0000,,B-But why my phone?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.13,0:09:36.34,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Any FBI investigator would've worked.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.67,0:09:40.24,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,If something happened to \NShibuya-sensei that night,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.24,0:09:43.87,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,the investigator whose \Nnumber was in her history
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.88,0:09:48.35,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,and Jodie-sensei would \Nbe called to the scene.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.63,0:09:49.83,DCMain,JODIE,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.16,0:09:56.86,DCMain,JODIE,0000,0000,0000,,From the beginning, they meant to get \Nintel from the agent who accompanied me.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.49,0:10:03.66,DCMain,JODIE,0000,0000,0000,,But Natsuko was injured after Kandachi-san \Npushed her down the park stairs.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.00,0:10:06.41,DCMain,JODIE,0000,0000,0000,,What if that hadn't happened?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.83,0:10:09.88,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe they meant to hit her with a car.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.50,0:10:13.30,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Bourbon said he was driving his.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.02,0:10:19.54,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Either way, they meant \Nto injure her outdoors.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.54,0:10:20.68,DCMain,JODIE,0000,0000,0000,,Outdoors?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.94,0:10:25.10,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, so they'd know how you were dressed.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.36,0:10:26.87,DCMain,JODIE,0000,0000,0000,,How I'm dressed?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.87,0:10:30.94,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,They can prepare a mask from photos,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.24,0:10:33.60,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,but that doesn't work for the \Noutfit you're wearing today.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.21,0:10:43.33,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,It's easier to see and take pictures of you if\Nyou're outside than in a building or a car.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.60,0:10:46.33,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Once the disguise was ready,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.73,0:10:52.50,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,they called to say Shibuya-sensei took a turn\Nfor the worse, bringing you to the hospital.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.10,0:10:58.51,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,They drew Camel's attention \Nto separate him from you.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.07,0:11:05.49,DCMain,JODIE,0000,0000,0000,,So Vermouth, disguised as me, \Ncould get information out of you.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.49,0:11:07.31,DCMain,CAMEL,0000,0000,0000,,S-Sorry...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.31,0:11:11.25,DCMain,JODIE,0000,0000,0000,,But, Conan-kun, when did you first notice?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.25,0:11:13.48,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,When the hospital called.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.91,0:11:18.27,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,A patient involved in the case could \Nhave information for the police.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.27,0:11:22.34,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,But they're only allowed to tell \Nrelatives about a patient's condition.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.34,0:11:25.41,DCMain,JODIE,0000,0000,0000,,Why didn't you tell me?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.41,0:11:27.82,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,I wasn't sure yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.82,0:11:31.52,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,It was possible she was \Ndisguised as Shibuya-sensei.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.52,0:11:32.68,DCMain,JODIE,0000,0000,0000,,Really?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.16,0:11:38.06,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,But what about Bourbon?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.16,0:11:42.86,DCMain,JODIE,0000,0000,0000,,What did you tell her?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.86,0:11:43.76,DCMain,CAMEL,0000,0000,0000,,Uh, right.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.10,0:11:50.69,DCMain,CAMEL,0000,0000,0000,,It was about Kusuda Rikumichi, their \Nspy who infiltrated the hospital.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.35,0:11:54.94,DCMain,CAMEL,0000,0000,0000,,That he shot himself inside his car.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.94,0:12:00.30,DCMain,JODIE,0000,0000,0000,,That's all?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.30,0:12:01.75,DCMain,CAMEL,0000,0000,0000,,Y-Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.75,0:12:07.12,DCMain,CAMEL,0000,0000,0000,,On the way here, Conan-kun drew my \Nattention to it, so it was on my mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.60,0:12:11.91,DCMain,JODIE,0000,0000,0000,,But how does that information help them?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.36,0:12:17.73,DCMain,CAMEL,0000,0000,0000,,If the man they thought was \Ncaptured by the FBI is dead,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.73,0:12:21.34,DCMain,CAMEL,0000,0000,0000,,they don't have to worry about him talking.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.73,0:12:25.24,DCMain,JODIE,0000,0000,0000,,Or could it mean something else?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.24,0:12:26.85,DCMain,JODIE,0000,0000,0000,,Right, Conan-kun?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.82,0:12:30.10,DCMain,JODIE,0000,0000,0000,,C-Conan-kun.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.32,0:12:39.35,DCMain,JODIE,0000,0000,0000,,Conan-kun?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.82,0:12:41.78,DCMain,JODIE,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Conan-kun?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.20,0:12:44.84,DCMain,JODIE,0000,0000,0000,,What's wrong, Conan-kun?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.64,0:12:55.79,DCMain,VERMOUTH,0000,0000,0000,,So who's Kusuda Rikumichi?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.16,0:12:58.87,DCMain,VERMOUTH,0000,0000,0000,,He was a member of the Organization.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.63,0:13:05.93,DCMain,VERMOUTH,0000,0000,0000,,But what does it matter if a man \Nwithout a code name shot himself?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.56,0:13:15.69,DCMain,AMURO,0000,0000,0000,,How would you kill yourself with a gun?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.98,0:13:22.86,DCMain,VERMOUTH,0000,0000,0000,,Well, I'd place the muzzle against my temple.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.47,0:13:31.18,DCMain,AMURO,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, leaving a clear bullet hole in \Nyour skull even if your body burned.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.69,0:13:32.54,DCMain,VERMOUTH,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.57,0:13:39.08,DCMain,AMURO,0000,0000,0000,,Don't you remember?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.37,0:13:44.20,DCMain,AMURO,0000,0000,0000,,When Kusuda disappeared,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.35,0:13:55.40,DCMain,AMURO,0000,0000,0000,,there was another man who was \Nshot in the head and burned.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.87,0:14:00.23,DCMain,VERMOUTH,0000,0000,0000,,Y-You don't mean...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.72,0:14:07.24,DCMain,AMURO,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. FBI investigator...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.66,0:14:13.67,DCMain,AMURO,0000,0000,0000,,...Akai Shuichi.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.26,0:14:20.48,DCMain,VERMOUTH,0000,0000,0000,,Impossible!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.05,0:14:23.29,DCMain,VERMOUTH,0000,0000,0000,,You're saying he's alive?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.66,0:14:27.24,DCMain,AMURO,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, if I'm right.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.66,0:14:37.85,DCMain,VERMOUTH,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry, but you're wrong.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.18,0:14:42.27,DCMain,VERMOUTH,0000,0000,0000,,His death was confirmed.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.70,0:14:49.38,DCMain,VERMOUTH,0000,0000,0000,,Confirmed by the Japanese police \Nat the request of the FBI.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.59,0:14:52.61,DCMain,VERMOUTH,0000,0000,0000,,Didn't I tell you?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.61,0:14:55.66,DCMain,VERMOUTH,0000,0000,0000,,The fingerprints from Akai's \Ncorpse that Kir shot in the head
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.87,0:14:59.38,DCMain,VERMOUTH,0000,0000,0000,,at Raiha Pass, and burned\Nalong with his car,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.77,0:15:05.17,DCMain,VERMOUTH,0000,0000,0000,,matched Akai's fingerprints left \Non the detective boy's phone.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.70,0:15:10.65,DCMain,AMURO,0000,0000,0000,,I see. But how did you get \Nfingerprints from a charred body?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.65,0:15:16.93,DCMain,VERMOUTH,0000,0000,0000,,Because he burned with his hand stuck inside \Nthe pocket of his flame retardant jacket.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.32,0:15:19.09,DCMain,VERMOUTH,0000,0000,0000,,That's the kind of man he was.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.61,0:15:24.06,DCMain,VERMOUTH,0000,0000,0000,,When he shot me with a shotgun, \Nhe had one hand in his pocket.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.34,0:15:30.45,DCMain,AMURO,0000,0000,0000,,Shooting a shotgun one-handed?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.45,0:15:31.70,DCMain,AMURO,0000,0000,0000,,Sounds like him.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.21,0:15:39.70,DCMain,AMURO,0000,0000,0000,,But it's possible the hand was in the \Npocket so you'd find fingerprints later.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.11,0:15:45.21,DCMain,VERMOUTH,0000,0000,0000,,If you doubt me so much, would you like to \Nsee a video of the moment Akai was shot?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:45.63,0:15:52.05,DCMain,AMURO,0000,0000,0000,,You mean the movie taken by the \Nhidden camera on Kir's neck?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.30,0:15:58.60,DCMain,VERMOUTH,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. You can clearly see \Nhim draw his last breath.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.42,0:16:08.06,DCItalic,VODKA,0000,0000,0000,,What's wrong, Kir?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.06,0:16:09.86,DCItalic,VODKA,0000,0000,0000,,Finish him.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.86,0:16:12.74,DCMain,KIR,0000,0000,0000,,But I shot him in the lung.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.13,0:16:16.01,DCItalic,KIR,0000,0000,0000,,Even if I leave him, he should \Nonly last about thirty minutes.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.23,0:16:18.24,DCItalic,VODKA,0000,0000,0000,,The head.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.94,0:16:21.50,DCItalic,VODKA,0000,0000,0000,,Shoot him in the head.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.95,0:16:25.63,DCItalic,VODKA,0000,0000,0000,,Then we'll know for certain his life is over.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.63,0:16:26.89,DCItalic,KIR,0000,0000,0000,,Roger that.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.96,0:16:47.65,DCMain,VERMOUTH,0000,0000,0000,,Before she shot him in the head, he said...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.08,0:16:53.49,DCItalic,AKAI,0000,0000,0000,,To think you went this far...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.06,0:16:56.14,DCItalic,KIR,0000,0000,0000,,I'm surprised, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.80,0:17:11.85,DCMain,VERMOUTH,0000,0000,0000,,Speaking as a fellow actor, \Nhe hadn't planned to say that.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.85,0:17:14.19,DCMain,VERMOUTH,0000,0000,0000,,It's what he truly felt.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.64,0:17:15.97,DCMain,VERMOUTH,0000,0000,0000,,It wasn't a performance.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.72,0:17:22.24,DCMain,VERMOUTH,0000,0000,0000,,But I'm disappointed you \Ndragged me into this farce.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.97,0:17:26.98,DCMain,AMURO,0000,0000,0000,,To think you went this far...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:28.27,0:17:31.73,DCMain,AMURO,0000,0000,0000,,To think you went this far...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.90,0:17:35.78,DCMain,AMURO,0000,0000,0000,,To think you went this far...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.87,0:17:39.77,DCItalic,AKAI,0000,0000,0000,,To think you went this far...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.59,0:17:49.14,DCMain,AMURO,0000,0000,0000,,I see. So that's how it is...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.47,0:18:00.18,DCMain,AMURO,0000,0000,0000,,I'll prove to you whether or not \NI'm right beyond any question.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:00.59,0:18:06.19,DCMain,VERMOUTH,0000,0000,0000,,So you know where to find his ghost?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.19,0:18:08.56,DCMain,AMURO,0000,0000,0000,,No, not yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.93,0:18:21.16,DCMain,AMURO,0000,0000,0000,,But once I get a lead, it'll take \Nme less than a day to investigate.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.93,0:18:49.72,DCMain,AYUMI,0000,0000,0000,,Did Conan-kun stay home from school today?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.72,0:18:52.98,DCMain,HAIBARA,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. He's in bed with a cold.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.98,0:18:56.85,DCMain,GENTA,0000,0000,0000,,What? But we're having curry for lunch today!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.85,0:18:58.40,DCMain,MITSUHIKO,0000,0000,0000,,You're worried about that?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.40,0:19:00.22,DCMain,GENTA,0000,0000,0000,,But it's curry!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.22,0:19:01.98,DCMain,GENTA,0000,0000,0000,,It even comes with pudding!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.08,0:19:05.95,DCItalic,HAIBARA,0000,0000,0000,,He was sneaking around with \Nthe professor last night.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.95,0:19:08.82,DCItalic,HAIBARA,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not sure he actually has a cold.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.59,0:19:25.61,DCNote,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(1,710)}Mori Detective Agency
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.07,0:19:27.35,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,Conan-kun!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.85,0:19:31.40,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,When do the Macademy Awards start?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.40,0:19:32.77,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,Wait, what?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.35,0:19:37.25,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,Dad, Conan-kun's still not home from school?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.61,0:19:43.32,DCMain,MORI,0000,0000,0000,,He called to say he was staying at the \Nprofessor's place so he didn't need dinner.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.76,0:19:44.82,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,No way!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.82,0:19:48.62,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,We were going to watch the \NMacademy Awards together...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.95,0:19:54.16,DCMain,MORI,0000,0000,0000,,Who cares about a foreign \Nfilm award ceremony?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.16,0:20:00.52,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,But Shinichi's dad is nominated \Nfor Best Original Script!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.52,0:20:02.01,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,Isn't it exciting?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.25,0:20:07.14,DCMain,MORI,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe for you, but why would that kid care?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.82,0:20:12.27,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,I guess you're right...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.27,0:20:15.49,DCMain,MORI,0000,0000,0000,,Sheesh. Anyway, get dinner on the table!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.49,0:20:17.52,DCMain,MORI,0000,0000,0000,,I'm starving here!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:23.20,0:20:26.53,DCItalic,TV,0000,0000,0000,,Let's start with Best Supporting Actor.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.79,0:20:32.64,DCItalic,TV,0000,0000,0000,,Presenting this year's award is \Nlast year's winner, Johnny Bip.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.29,0:20:37.08,DCNote,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,Kudo
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.05,0:20:47.12,DCMain,OKIYA,0000,0000,0000,,Yes?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.12,0:20:48.47,DCItalic,AMURO,0000,0000,0000,,Delivery.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:52.33,0:20:53.77,DCMain,AMURO,0000,0000,0000,,Good evening.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.77,0:20:56.94,DCMain,AMURO,0000,0000,0000,,Nice to meet you. I'm Amuro Toru.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:57.60,0:20:58.72,DCMain,OKIYA,0000,0000,0000,,I see...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:59.47,0:21:04.91,DCMain,AMURO,0000,0000,0000,,But this isn't the first \Ntime we've met, is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:30.33,0:22:32.41,DCMain,AMURO,0000,0000,0000,,I'd like to talk.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:32.41,0:22:34.66,DCMain,AMURO,0000,0000,0000,,May I come in?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:34.66,0:22:37.20,DCMain,OKIYA,0000,0000,0000,,Sure, but just you.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:37.73,0:22:43.76,DCMain,OKIYA,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry, but could your \Nfriends wait outside?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:45.08,0:22:48.88,DCMain,OKIYA,0000,0000,0000,,I don't think I have enough teacups.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:50.24,0:22:52.02,DCMain,AMURO,0000,0000,0000,,Don't worry about them.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:52.38,0:22:54.89,DCMain,AMURO,0000,0000,0000,,They like waiting outside.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:55.68,0:23:03.90,DCMain,AMURO,0000,0000,0000,,But depending on your answers, \Nwe may all end up coming in.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:06.73,0:23:09.15,DCMain,CAMEL,0000,0000,0000,,R-Raiha Pass?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:09.48,0:23:13.91,DCMain,CAMEL,0000,0000,0000,,We're going to the place \Nwhere they killed Akai-san?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:14.32,0:23:15.21,DCMain,JODIE,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:15.79,0:23:18.50,DCMain,JODIE,0000,0000,0000,,I think we'll find something there.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:18.69,0:23:25.24,DCMain,JODIE,0000,0000,0000,,That expression he made when he learned \Nthey'd learned Kusuda shot himself.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:26.00,0:23:30.50,DCMain,JODIE,0000,0000,0000,,And the way he lost his cool during \Nthe flower viewing incident.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:30.50,0:23:33.66,DCMain,JODIE,0000,0000,0000,,There's must be something there.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:44.94,0:24:08.96,DCEpPreview,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,Episode Preview
Dialogue: 0,0:23:45.62,0:23:47.57,DCMain,AMURO,0000,0000,0000,,Do you like mysteries?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:48.09,0:23:50.07,DCMain,AMURO,0000,0000,0000,,Let's start there, then.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:50.44,0:23:56.95,DCMain,OKIYA,0000,0000,0000,,But the dead man touched that \Nphone after the thin man, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:59.07,0:24:06.71,DCMain,CAMEL,0000,0000,0000,,But Akai-san touched that phone before we \Nallowed them to recover Mizunashi Rena.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:08.96,0:24:14.97,DCNextEp,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,The Scarlet Return
Dialogue: 0,0:24:09.68,0:24:13.13,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,The next episode of Conan \Nis "The Scarlet Return!"
Dialogue: 0,0:24:29.98,0:24:34.99,Hint,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,Raiha Pass
Dialogue: 0,0:24:30.53,0:24:32.41,DCMain,AMURO,0000,0000,0000,,Next Conan's hint:
Dialogue: 0,0:24:32.41,0:24:34.68,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Raiha Pass!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:34.99,0:24:37.43,DCMain,AMURO,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}You think Okiya-san likes \Nthe Macademy Awards?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:34.99,0:24:39.98,Don'tMiss,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,Don't miss the next episode.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:37.43,0:24:39.83,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}To think he'd be this big of a fan, right?
